SIMPLE: regardless
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Regardless
<hw>Re*gard"less</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having no regard;
heedless; careless; <as>as, <ex>regardless</ex> of life, consequences,
dignity</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Regardless</qex> of the bliss wherein he sat.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not regarded; slighted.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Spectator.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Heedless; negligent; careless; indifferent;
unconcerned; inattentive; unobservant; neglectful.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Re*gard"less*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Re*gard"less*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Regather</ent>⟦br⟧
